---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — robinson-cursor.com" description="What robinson-cursor.com is about and why it exists.">
  <article class="about">
    <h1>about</h1>

    <section>
      <h2>what is this?</h2>
      <p>
        365 days, 365 small web projects. Every day a new experiment —
        built in the browser, for the browser. No product, no startup.
        Just code, curiosity, and a self-imposed deadline.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>why?</h2>
      <p>
        Because you build things to understand them. Because daily constraints
        force creative solutions. And because a year of small experiments
        teaches more than six months of planning.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>how?</h2>
      <p>
        The archive site runs on <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a>,
        deployed via <a href="https://pages.cloudflare.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cloudflare Pages</a>.
        The daily projects themselves are framework-agnostic — plain HTML, Canvas, WebAudio,
        WebGL, p5.js, Three.js, React, whatever the experiment needs.
      </p>
      <p>
        Built with the help of AI tools. Source code is open:
        <a href="https://github.com/rxtxr/robinson-cursor" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com/rxtxr/robinson-cursor</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>license</h2>
      <p>
        All code and projects are released under the
        <a href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MIT License</a>.
        Fork it, remix it, build on it — just keep the attribution.
        Individual projects may use third-party libraries with their own licenses,
        documented in each project's metadata.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .about section {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .about h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .about p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
</style>
